```{r, include=FALSE}
graph=startGraph('http://localhost:7474/db/data', username='neo4j', password='admin')
query='
MATCH (a:Algorithm)
MATCH (c)-[:WASEVALWITH]->(a)
AND (c)-[:ISANEVALOF]->(b)
WHERE b.
RETURN c.tNoise, b.tEval
'
q<-cypher(graph,query)#takes all the info on time vs 
```

You can also embed plots, for example:

```{r, echo=FALSE}
plot(cars)
```

Note that the `echo = FALSE` parameter was added to the code chunk to prevent printing of the R code that generated the plot.
